anna ly transformative learning technologies laboratory home about publications projects people teaching media fablearn 2011 home people anna ly anna ly position alumni anna is currently a master's student in the learning design and technology program before she came to stanford she worked as an ibm strategy and transformation consultant in ny she has a degree in human computer interaction and business from carnegie mellon and a minor in communication design her interests lie in user interface experience design use of educational technologies in developing countries affordable technologies storytelling video games expressive and tangible technologies constructionist learning environments social entrepreneurship design thinking in schools and informal learning contexts a lot of areas outside of school she loves getting involved in social design groups such as project m on the side she coordinates weddings and owns her own event and wedding paper design business she loves paper and fabric and making whatever she can out of it people faculty visiting researchers phd students ma students ms students undergraduate students high school interns collaborators alumni transformative learning technologies lab school of education stanford university 520 galvez mall room 102 ceras building stanford california 94305 usa connect with us connect with us on facebook connect with us on twitter connect with us on youtube connect with us on flickr copyright 2011 all rights reserved top
